FIG. 1 is a diagram showing a typical interference condition which can be remedied by the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a block diagram of the transmitter and receiver components in a typical communication channel;


FIG. 3 is a graphical representation of the effects of interference on a received signal;


FIG. 4 is a diagram showing the relative positions of a mobile unit, a source of interference, and a receiving base station employing antenna diversity;


FIG. 5 is a graphical representation of received carrier and interfering signal strength;


FIG. 6 is a graphical representation of received carrier and interfering signal strength, as adjusted according to the present invention;


FIG. 7 is a vector representation of the addition of two diversity branches;


FIG. 8 is a graphical representation showing the adjustment of the offset angle as an incremental adjustment; and


FIG. 9 is a diagram illustrating an interference condition in a fading environment.
